values:
i'm talking about alexander mc, of course.  




one day i'll know what to do.

ch ch chaaangessssss!
Lil Davey died.  Sorry for those of you who liked him.  As it turns out, he would rather ask why I'm wearing a dress than say I look nice.   If you catch my catch.  Also, I wasn't so nice to him.  THE END. 
So now I'm on an epic apt search.  Who can find the cheapest apt with a washer/dryer and hardwood floors?  Or, who wants the cheapest roommate?  This should be a gameshow.  What else is new.  Oh, work stuff.  Now I own the fry station along with the other two, and they even let me work grill.  I saute things that are on fire.  And they sent me, one other cook, and the kitchen manager to open a new location.  That's it. We kicked it's ass.  So basically, now I wear a chef coat, just for looks, not a real chef, but goddamnit I'm on the way!  Also, who thinks I should move away once I'm a manager at work and have a good deal of kitchen experience and have saved a few dollars?  Hmmm.  
Ufck it.  I'm going to be a traveling porn star.  Vanilla sex only.  Easiest.  Job.  Ever.

hey guys, remember livejournal? holy shit, me too.
it took several entries and guesses before i remembered my password/username. but i did it, yay me. ok. i knew my username cuz i still remembered someone else's livejournal address. Formerly known as Sleepless in Vermillion, it was yours.  If you even look at these things.
Well, kids.
I am not the blogger I once was.
Oh no.
I'm badass cook. And by badass cook, I mean that I do salads and desserts for an Irish Pub, and sometimes they let me work the fry station. And I helped name on of the sandwiches.  And my boss protects me from creepers at the bar. 
And I'm a barista in a super cafe.  All coffees served within a week of roasting. Fucking delicious, locally owned, sweeter espresso than everywhere else, and as long as my boobies aren't totally showing, I can wear whatever I please.
Like this sweet Barbie(tm) shirt.
Yes. It's trademarked. Actually the shirt doesn't have the trademark on it.  My Barbie is black and rocking a fro. Eat it, blondie.
Oh yeah, and, could someone remind me why I'm in Virginia?

sometimes people share their thoughts, and, drunk or sober, i wonder.
just how much of that was complete bollocks?
when can you be comfortable?
just say what you mean.
i swear you'll be happier.
then you won't bring the rest of us down with you.
drama queens.

my earring is crusty, my eyelids are drooping, my shoes are still on.

alarm goes off in 6 hours

and a half.

in the army people are trained to want to kill.

yelling that they want to kill somebody. daily occurence.

testosterones galore.

and i hear there are no hot chicks in georgia.

after a week and a half of tripping my balls off, and i mean road tripping, without psychedelic enhancement, here i am. and i still dunno what to do.  i have this job, right? and it's ok. they pay me. but that's all there is to keep me there. my brain is broken, i'm relatively certain.  strained to a point about 5 miles past exhaustion.  all that's left to do is just live. doing the daybyday thing. where's the dream?
maybe this doesn't make sense to whoever you are, dear reader, but it's coming out of my head and that must count for something. i'm going to bed.

so that was my travel journal.  a minimum of details.  i think a page is missing somewhere, cuz i'm almost certain i wrote about the 60 foot tall pop bottle in oklahoma. yes, pop. not soda.  they call the gift shop at that particular tourist trap on route 66 pop's.  it's this crazy glass building with walls of soda bottles.  50's diner decor, jukebox oldies. thanks to sheridan for making me the journal.  sadly the content is undeserving of the beautiful art that is the journal itself.

Mr. Pickles is a sandwich shop w/in walking distance of my new home.  The Man said it's soccer moms out here, & the piercings just don't fly.  So...they'll call me.  Here @ Ben's *bucks.  Yeah. I know.  sellouttime & my sellout corporate coffee.  I'm on a 3-latte-a-day diet.  I can't make any excuses for myself.  Shit.  If they at least had in-house cups or something

Is this a test to see how much I can tolerate?  As of right exactly now, I don't think I can live with these people.  They want me to get a haircut, to look Normal. just like everyone else in this godforsaken yuppy haven of a suburb.  Christ.  Diane & Unity want me to get an "update"  Translation:  LA makeover.  Gross.  Super Superficiality makes me want to scream and vomit in their faces & on their trendy jackets and shoes.

FUCK.

Sorry I neglected you, dear journal.  Went to LALAland.  Saw Diane Keaton, Topher Grace & Stevie Wonder on Hollywood Blvd.  woo.  Nina is insane.  Democratic Convention in Hollywood. Crazy.  Protesters & speakers w/disappointingly small crowd spoke for the cholla, but hear blar blar blar.  Didn't hear much of what they said.  But really, I don't know if I can live here for 9 NINE months.

Uh. Yeah.  Been sitting still on the I-40 so long that Butch is off.  hazard lights are on.  My Guess is that they're clearing away the accident caused by the whiteout conditions here.  I40 East has just started to have traffic.  WOOT.  Maybe we will, too. 
And I thought I'd never use my ice scraper again.  Ha!
Well, I have 3 granola bars & 6 8oz bottles of water.  So I can survive for a while, if need be.  If I sit here for a week til the weather clears up.  JESUSFUCK.  This Blows.

If you're going to get stuck on I-40 for an hour, make SURE you use the bathroom first.  Also, it's probably not a good idea to pee in your travel mug b/c A)What if it overflows? and 2)  You may want to used it for coffee later and no one wants to drink coffee out of something that was peed in.  MUG--->[see actual journal for picture]

Stuck on I-40 is a good time to update your travel journal.  Or write a novel.  Or smoke a joint w/the trucker stuck behind you.

Definitely losing track of what day it is.  Wednesday.  So I went to Texas Yesterday.  Sadly, it wasn't as scary & BIG as I had hoped.  The Welcome sign says
"Drive Friendly--the Texas Way"
I-40 is 70 in day, 65 at night.  LAME.  it was just me and a bunch of trucks.  I saw one van of old ladies from Minnesota driving as fast as possible, presumable to get the hell outta there.  The sky in TX is Huuuuuuuuge

"Why so down?  It'll only get worse before it gets better...Smile, Young Lady!"
"How come you never smile?"
"Cuz if I did, everyone would think I was sick!"
-Denny's, NM.

New Mexico's Santa Rosa Denny's seems to be full of nice people.  I kinda want to get to know them.

McLean Texas is DEAD.  Gas Station Guy killed it for me.

A few miles down the road is the largest cross in the world...in the western hemisphere.

it's like tha Grille meets Market St. and expands. snow and wind.  jesus. Thought I left all that in S.D.  At El Dorado Lake, the interstate looks like it's in a puddle -------------->[see actual journal for picture] & the tops of bare trees stick up out of the water.
Thought I could make it to OK city by noon, but maybe not.  I was going to see a Museum in old town Wichita w/DINOSAURS but the snow is just too ridiculous.  I have no fucking idea where it is.  Oh well. breakfast at the Diner, then off again.

Holy shit.  I'm in fucking KANSAS!  Drove away from Vermillion with mixed feelings.  Mostly ecstasy.  I said Goodbye to EVERYTHING.  So free. Soooooooo free. Not a lot of interesting sights today.  There was a neat watertower in Misery.  Sapp Bros. {see actual journal for picture] EconoLodge w/stained cushions and 4-lock doors.

it's thursday, i do have a job, and technically i have shit to do. i could be going to san francisco on sunday...sadly, i'll instead be learning how to ring up gasoline and lotto tickets, organizing energy drinks, and taking smoke breaks.  balls.  but i do have a job now, so i guess i shouldn't complain. or at least complain less.  someone needs to intervene about me and online quizzes. croikee.

heather howitz --
[adjective]:

Like in nature to a train-riding hobo
'How will you be defined in the dictionary?' at QuizGalaxy.com

INFP - "Questor". High capacity for caring. Emotional face to the world. High sense of honor derived from internal values. 4.4% of total population.

someone pat me on the back, cuz i just deleted my facebook account. hell. yeah. i feel unburdened.  also, i chose not to respond to a boy making me feel bad for not wanting to talk to him.  i don't wanna talk to him cuz he fucks with my head. bully for me.  also, my family and i ran up a 
$600
yes. 
$600
bill at a fondue restaurant.  4 courses. cheese fondue followed by salad, then the entree, then dessert fondue.  and the wine. oh, the wine.  it's called seven deadly zins.  cheesy name, yes. delicious, yes. perfect, yes. curry sauce with entree, also perfect. not too spicy, a yellow curry with coconut. smoothtastic. i want to be proposed to over fondue.  if, at all during the meal, he or she drops something from the fork into the pot, no wedding.  i also got to witness my brother being loud and drunk. and hilarious.  and my sisters tearing each other to shreds. verbally, of course. we were in public.  we stayed over an hour after the restaurant closed, but we were on the third course when closing time came around, so.....  i dunno if i feel worse for the waitress or for the friend of the family who had to sit there rather awkwardly.  hmm. but the food was amazing. 
so if i read books and travel the world, i'll still be smart?
or
if i go to school and study abroad, i'll have a rich education?
or
i'll build me a shack with a little garden outside and write my books and from the world i'll hide?

i remember being somewhat more excited about this holiday last year.  hmmm...whatever.  i still don't have a job...and i still haven't posted my travel journal up on this thang....and i think i want to move to portland. what?  if there's anybody out there, i give you  my permission to decide my life for me.  or i could get married.  someone wants to marry me. isn't that nice? two someones, even.  i think.   at least one.  yeah. that'll solve my decision-making dilemma.  yarp.  blerblerbler.blar blarblar.  i bought new shoes but i can't walk like a normal person so does it really matter if wear them? i hobble.  my knee says fuck you really loudly and painfully every time i bend it or walk on it....or anything. balls. balls balls balls.  tristan. email me. it's been days and i feel so alone......boohoo.


and to all the vermillion villains, have a lovely today and tomorrow and the next day.  you are missed.

we're just one big sad monster four legs four arms two heads two noses.


it's like a kevin bacon-athon over here.  first there was tremors, and then this crazyawesome movie called digging to china which you watch and in the back of your mind you're like, i know who that kid is who is it who does she grow up to be and it's freakin' evan rachel wood. whoa.

i finished my scholarship apps! wooooooooooo! someone applaud me. please? also, i got an interview at mr. pickles today. no, not that kind. it's a sandwich shop.  holy goodness it's like i live here and i'm actually going to school this time. no cold feet. please? make them go away.

here i am, eating new york cheddar with herbs kettle chips for breakfast. nicely compliments the weak dbl latte that tasted like milk.  sheena is a punkrocker now.  i've developed this incredible need to turn my niece baylie into a superhardcorepunkrockpirateprincess.  she already knows how to hit people in the face and knock off their glasses.  or maybe she just does that to me.  at any rate, at least she's not telling me to get a real haircut, like the other fembots around here.  communists.  i'll blow smoke in all their faces.  well. no. i won't.  but i think i'll stop showering completely and only wear things that would make their fragile fashion senses cringe and squibble.

coming up soon:  travel journal from freakin oklahoma or somewhere like that. texas and kansas.  3.5 hours of sitting still in the mountains of new mexico because of a snowstorm and a wicked awesome accident at mile 44 of i40.

also, i love the ramones right now.

MYSTIC BEAUTY - You are eccentric, enigmatic, and intriguing. You keep to yourself and so no one knows the real you. You prefer the solace and quiet of your own company over big crowds of people. You are highly intelligent but you do everything your own way. You come off as quirky or weird and most people don't understand you at all. You are probably a little disorganized. You probably also seem distant and dreamy but that's because you're off in your own little world.

i think i'm going on a rescue mission tomorrow. so. yay? also, my sister told me that one day i'd have to start thinking realistically. heartbreak. what a douche.

yes.
i don't know.
but it will happen.
don't you worry.


i think i am going to pee my pants. or vomit on your shoes. i can't decide which would be more satisfying. probably the vomit one.

gag*choke*vomit

spinspinspin

waaaaaaahoooooooooooo!

and i guess i'll just keep riding til i crash

ok, since tristan mentioned it...
so he came and he talked and he cried and i talked and i cried because we're both kind of miserable in general, the fact that we've broken up notwithstanding. the boy needs to be institutionalized. then ian came over and he felt awkward so ian left and then nick left b ut only after chainsmokingly telling me how stupid he is and that he doesn't expect us to get back together or anything, he's just miserable and doesn't have a reason to live.
and um. well. after the whole ian dui semi-prank thing i decided that i'd rather not devote my time to making other people feel better. who's gonna make me feel better? i can't do that for more than one person at a time, and i win. so. yay me.
hopefully the guy from the gallery in yankton likes my photos...then i'll have done something neato. and wholly un-depressing. sort of.

but there's a scratch on my arm. 
i was pissed, then i was drunk, then i was pissdrunk.
crazy.
i was driving.
i looked through the rear view mirror, but the window was foggy.
crazy.

never ever make them. it's a terrible experience. i found this recipe for honey oat pancakes and i was like, ooh, honey oat pancakes. but we had no buttermilk so i used raspberry yogurt instead, thinking it would make a delicious pancake. what happened was a batter that was more like cookie dough that had to be carefully spread onto a buttered pan so that it would cook all the way through and not just burn the outsides, leaving the middle all gooey. eventually i started treating the batter like scrambled eggs. i'm calling it granola. i bet it would be delicious sprinkled over some poached peaches a la mode.
damnit. i hate pancakes.

seriously. it makes so much more sense that trying to accomplish anything that could be considered "meaningful" or whatever.  so i'm back in the lap of luxury at the house of my parents.  laundry, free food, cold house, lots of blankets even though it's 3 million degrees out sometimes. one day i'll grow up and attempt responsibility. i must not be ready yet, cuz my family keeps doing things for me. i appreciate it, yes, but i hope that they realize it may be hindering my ability to do anything for myself and to get out of this mess my head is in. ah well. it doesn't matter anyway.  but as for supercool things, savannahhobodanianphiljonahjessicamattgeoffreyallychristinetaianakyletellfoleybrandontristancoffeeshopgallerykids
and much more still exist. which is nice.
yay for you guys, i'd be lost without you.

there's a photo contest in yankton. it might already be over, since there was no date on the flyer. but if it's not, i'm going to try. i hope i do.  so. gotta get some kids out on the river cuz the themething is Life on the River.  i've never seen as much life on the river as when we go there. yes.

gooddayall.

So here I am,  checking up on the ol' LJ and the ol' Myspace and even the not ol' Facebook when  I should be getting ready for work. But you see my friends, summer has arrived. Ah, yes, summer: that overly warm time of year when a young girl's fancy turns to the internet.

and. in closing:
I love minigherkins and baby carrots.  Viciously crunching up tiny phallic symbols with the sharpest of my incisors makes me feel that somewhere, somehow, something is going just swimmingly in this human-dominated used-to-be-cool-but-now-sucks nuclear shithole of a planet.
